   <abstract>1824, July 20, V.B.M., Baltimore, Md., to J.G.M. Ramsey, near Knoxville, Tenn. Expresses the writer&apos;s interest in history of the Mecklenburg Convention and gives advice on how best to record history. Also features a discussion of books. Encloses a sermon by the Rev. Mr. Duncan (missing) and discusses Rev. Duncan&apos;s admirable but controversial methods.</abstract>
